law.text:
As a requirement for keeping the facility permit, each facility permit holder shall:
Maintain a bond or other security that the Department considers sufficient to cover any cost for:
Guaranteeing fulfillment of all requirements related to the facility permit;
Monitoring, maintaining, or closing the facility; and
Assuring the security of the facility after closing;
Design, construct, and operate the facility in the manner approved by the Department;
Establish emergency procedures and safeguards to prevent accidents and reasonably foreseeable harm to human beings or the environment;
Report periodically on the hazardous material that is received and transferred by the facility, including, as applicable, volume, and chemical, physical, biological, and radioactive nature; and
To the extent reasonably practicable, restore the facility site to its original condition if use as a facility is terminated.
